{
  "texts": [
    "Another drawback of using fully connected layers for decoding is the challenge of expanding spatial resolution.",
    "For predictions at higher resolutions, such as 32× 32 or 64×64, the parameters that must be trained for the fully connected layers will grow exponentially.",
    "In general, using a more powerful encoder network can better extract features from wave field signals relevant to cracks.",
    "However, the selection of the encoder network regarding the scale and complexity still requires careful consideration.",
    "Larger networks have more trainable parameters, which demand more data and robust training methods."
  ]
}